   https://oauth.provider.com/authorize?redirect_uri=https://attacker.com/steal
```

**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- Hardcoded secrets can be extracted from source control or binaries
- Missing state parameter validation enables CSRF attacks
- No token signature or issuer validation allows forged tokens
- No audience validation means tokens for other apps work here
- Wildcard or loose redirect URI validation enables token theft

**SECURE VERSION**:

